  "notes": "Table saison inspired by Hitachino Nest Saison du Japon and Saison Dupont. Low ABV but drinks bigger than its gravity. High mash temp for body, structured fermentation ramp for glycerol and phenol production. Brew on Ss Brewtech SVBS.\n\nWater: Build from distilled water with brewing salts. Target chloride-forward profile (Cl:SO4 ~1.5:1) for malt perception and body.\n\nFermentation: Start cool (68°F/20°C), ramp 3-4°F/day to 78-80°F (25.6-26.7°C). M29 doesn't need extreme temps like 3724. Total fermentation ~2-3 weeks.\n\nDry hop Hallertau Blanc for 3 days max — goes grassy past that.\n\nHigh carbonation (3.0-3.2 vol) is critical — transforms mouthfeel from thin table beer to lively farmhouse ale.\n\nv1 Lessons: Mosaic/Galaxy were too fruity, 149°F mash was too fermentable, 2.4 vol CO2 was too flat, Belle Saison was too clean.",

